OL,3,CWhy do people stalk? From 'goal
OL,4,Corientation' to 'addiction'
OL,6,FBut what actually compels people to
OL,7,Fstalk?
OL,9,FJane Monckton Smith, a Professor of
OL,10,FPublic Protection at the University of
OL,11,FGloucestershire who is internationally
OL,12,Frenowned for her research into
OL,13,Fhomicide, coercive control and
OL,14,Fstalking, told ITV West Country
OL,15,Fstalking can be 'goal oriented'.
OL,17,FShe explained: "So stalking can be
OL,18,Fgoal oriented so that they have a
OL,19,Fgoal. It's not just random. They are
OL,20,Factually trying to achieve something
OL,21,Fwith that stalking.
OL,26,@yD@POU
OL,1,W~s1j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G2/10
OL,2,W,.!+.-' "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BSW Eng NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,437,430,120,260,000,100
PN,43603
SC,0003
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F436A1777299067
OL,3,CWhy do people stalk? From 'goal
OL,4,Corientation' to 'addiction'
OL,6,F"So a very simple goal might be, for
OL,7,Fexample, I want to make this person
OL,8,Freally scared, or I want to destroy
OL,9,Ftheir reputation. I want them to be
OL,10,Fpublicly destroyed."
OL,12,FLydia Little, a researcher in
OL,13,FPsychological Trauma who works for
OL,14,FFearFree, added: "There is something
OL,15,Funusual about stalking.
OL,17,F"We've looked and looked and looked at
OL,18,Fall of our cases to try and predict
OL,19,Fwhen this may happen, because
OL,20,Fobviously that's an important part of
OL,21,Fsafeguarding people.
OL,26,@nD@AOUrD@TO]
OL,1,W~s1j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G3/10
