FL,437,430,120,260,000,100
PN,43605
SC,0005
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F436A1777299067
OL,3,CWhy do people stalk? From 'goal
OL,4,Corientation' to 'addiction'
OL,6,FRejected: Someone who is unable to let
OL,7,Fgo following the breakdown of a
OL,8,Frelationship. Often driven by revenge
OL,9,Fand hopes of a reconciliation, they
OL,10,Ftarget their ex-partners and sometimes
OL,11,Fthose close to them as well.
OL,13,FResentful: When a person seeks to
OL,14,Fcontrol by instilling fear or seeks
OL,15,Frevenge for perceived wrongs. These
OL,16,Fstalkers are often paranoid or
OL,17,Fdelusional and can target
OL,18,Facquaintances or strangers.
OL,1,W~s1j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G5/10
OL,2,W,.!+.-' "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BSW Eng NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,437,430,120,260,000,100
PN,43606
SC,0006
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F436A1777299067
OL,3,CWhy do people stalk? From 'goal
OL,4,Corientation' to 'addiction'
OL,6,FIntimacy seeker: Someone who craves an
OL,7,Femotional connection. These people
OL,8,Foften target strangers and can be
OL,9,Fdelusional and lonely.
OL,11,FIncompetent Suitor: An often socially
OL,12,Fawkward person who is persistent in
OL,13,Fcommunication and frequently misreads
OL,14,Fsignals. These people may target
OL,15,Facquaintances or strangers and may not
OL,16,Frealise the harm they are causing.
OL,18,FPredatory: A person who stalks for
OL,19,Fsexual gratification or violence,
OL,20,Foften targets women that are strangers.
OL,1,W~s1j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G6/10
OL,2,W,.!+.-' "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,
